import Mathlib

/-- Let U ‚äÜ ‚ÑÇ be a domain (open and connected) and f : U ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ holomorphic (differentiable on U).
If f(z0) = c and f'(z0) = 0, then either f ‚â° c on U or else z0 is a zero of f - c of order m,
and there exists a neighborhood V of z0 such that f^{-1}({c}) ‚à© V consists of exactly m points (with multiplicity).

This statement formalizes the local factorization version: locally f(z) - c = (z - z0)^m * g(z) with g(z0) ‚â† 0.
-/
theorem holomorphic_zero_of_critical_point {U : Set ‚ÑÇ} (hU_open : IsOpen U) (hU_conn : IsConnected U)
  {f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ} (hf : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ f U) {z0 : ‚ÑÇ} (hz0U : z0 ‚àà U) {c : ‚ÑÇ} (hc : f z0 = c)
  (hder : deriv f z0 = 0) :
  (‚àÄ z ‚àà U, f z = c) ‚à®
  ‚àÉ (m : ‚Ñï) (hm : 0 < m) (V : Set ‚ÑÇ) (hV_open : IsOpen V) (hz0V : z0 ‚àà V) (hVsub : V ‚äÜ U)
    (g : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ) (hg : DifferentiableOn ‚ÑÇ g V) (hg0 : g z0 ‚â† 0)
    (hfac : ‚àÄ ‚¶Éz‚¶Ñ, z ‚àà V ‚Üí f z - c = (z - z0) ^ m * g z) := by sorry
